{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5a83a935-2e24-48f7-9817-81cb2ef4e585","content":"In MSTest v4, `[ExpectedException]` was removed. Replace it with **`Assert.ThrowsException<T>`** (or its async counterpart):\n\n**Before (v3):**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]\npublic void Foo_NullArg_Throws()\n{\n    MyClass.Foo(null);\n}\n```\n\n**After (v4):**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void Foo_NullArg_Throws()\n{\n    Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(() => MyClass.Foo(null));\n}\n```\n\nFor **async** methods, use:\n```csharp\nawait Assert.ThrowsExceptionAsync<ArgumentNullException>(\n    () => MyClass.FooAsync(null));\n```\n\n**Why the change?** `Assert.ThrowsException` is more precise — it scopes the assertion to the exact call you expect to throw, rather than the entire method body. This avoids false passes when a *different* line throws the same exception type.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9cef1a07-b997-439e-816e-58865f547a19","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from MSTest v3 to v4, specifically about the `[ExpectedException]` attribute which has been removed. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to search any codebase.","outputTokens":333,"requestId":"4C12:326A6D:33BCF3:3CBEAB:6A0145CD"},"id":"48002c8f-60a7-4552-a08b-3898c534326e","timestamp":"2026-05-11T02:58:30.137Z","parentId":"713a4e8a-f8e8-48cb-86c2-e34eda507dc6"}
